                  $\sim$1/2 of the pseudoenergy flux. This is
                  consistent with other studies, in particular Moum et
                  al 2006 and Scotti et al 2006, and reinforces that
                  much of the internal wave energy generated by
                  tide-topography interaction ends up in the high
                  frequency nonhydrostatic ISW field.  },
