                  of internal waves. Highly accurate measurements of
                  wave propagation speeds and directions are
                  possible. The applicability of various weakly
                  nonlinear theories in modeling propagation of the
                  observed large-amplitude waves is tested. The
                  measured wave speeds enable us to differentiate
                  between classic internal wave models. The linear,
                  KdV (Korteweg-de Vries), and BO (Benjamin-Ono)
                  models are applied with and without background
                  shear. After background shear effects are included,
